@17   = ~Dwarven Smith~
@18   = ~ DWARVEN SMITH: In the halls of dwarven clans, mastery in craftsmanship is considered to be the most prestigious profession. The other races know dwarves first and foremost to be fearless miners and talented smiths, the latter having gained worldwide fame for their masterfully crafted weapons. The typical Dwarven Smith is strong, tough and insensitive to heat after long hours working the forge. Being true masters of smithing they knows the secrets of any item at first glance. Dwarven Smiths will not hesitate to protect their forge from danger, and while they are familiar with most weapons from the training grounds, in battle they mostly rely on hammers and axes.

Advantages:
- Gains 1% resistance to fire every level (starting at 5%)
- Increased lore
- Gains special ability Ghost Hammer

Disadvantages:
- May achieve Grand Mastery only for Hammers and Axes
- May achieve Specialization only in Single Weapon Style~
