@182  = ~The History of Berronar's Axe~
@183  = ~In that time Moradin made his wife Berronar a glorious gift. One year and one day he forged a silver axe, to protect the clan, and to honor his beloved wife. Of flawless purity was the silver blade, honed with the finest materials, and in its center the ruby, sparkling and glowing like the evening sun.

And as she took the axe from Moradin's hands, light glistened in the halls of the Mordinsamman, and the sapphire on its tip glowed like a falling star.

But when Abbathor, the dark god of greed, saw the axe, he envied Berronar this weapon. He jumped her and ran away with it. Moradin took his hammer, ran after the thief and caught him.

And as Moradin's hammer came down with the force of a thousand avalanches, Abbathor raised the axe in defense. And behold, it withstood the blow! But the precious gems were broken from their sockets and fell into the realms of the mortals. The ruby, the sapphire and the emerald, who decorated the pommel, flew over mountains and valleys and disappeared in the Underdark, never to be seen again.~
